Brown capuchin monkeys travel through the forest being mischievous: they pull down wasp and termite nests and toss them down to the ground. They also throw down palm fronds and dead branches as they go. In abandoned swiddens they throw down peach-palm [

Bactris gasipaes

] fruits without eating them. At night they sleep in any tree that has vine tangles.
